The available POLYNOMIAL of INTERPOLATION are of
LAGRANGE and with a degree 1 or 2 in 2D, 3D and axisymmetric.

The NODES are the points which support the DEGREES of FREEDOM
of the FINITE ELEMENTS.

The POINTS  are the points which support the coordinates
to define the mapping
   F : REFERENCE FINITE ELEMENT -> CURRENT FINITE ELEMENT

The FINITE ELEMENT is said ISOPARAMETRIC if the same INTERPOLATION
is used for the unknown solution (Temperature, Component of
Displacement, ... ) and the components of F.

Here, all the programmed FINITE ELEMENTS are ISOPARAMETRIC.

The polynomials of degree 1 use VERTICES=NODES=POINTS.
The polynomials of degree 2 use VERTICES & MIDDLES of EDGES=NODES=POINTS.
